            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EHow%20quickly%20the%20enemy%20tries%20to%20sneak%20back%20into%20areas%20we%20have%20removed%20him%20from%20in%20the%20past!%20In%20the%20first%20chapters%20of%20Nehemiah%2C%20we%20see%20a%20man%20named%20Tobiah%20causing%20Nehemiah%20great%20problems.%20Nehemiah%20defeated%20him%2C%20yet%20sometime%20later%20we%20find%20Tobiah%20living%20in%20the%20temple%20where%20the%20tithes%20and%20offerings%20were%20kept!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWe%20should%20never%20lose%20our%20vigilance%20in%20fighting%20the%20devil.%20If%20we%20relax%20after%20a%20victory%2C%20he%20will%20try%20to%20sneak%20in%20the%20back%20door%20and%20continue%20his%20wickedness.%20Peter%20instructed%20us%20to%20be%20on%20guard%20against%20the%20devil%20because%20%22he%20prowls%20around%20like%20a%20roaring%20lion%2C%20looking%20for%20some%20victim%20to%20devour%22%20(1%20Peter%205%3A8).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAny%20house%20left%20vacant%20gradually%20falls%20into%20ruin.%20When%20Nehemiah%20returned%20to%20Jerusalem%2C%20he%20found%20that%20the%20tithes%20had%20not%20been%20paid%2C%20and%20the%20duties%20of%20the%20priesthood%20had%20been%20neglected.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20people%20had%20failed%20to%20keep%20the%20Sabbath%20and%20had%20even%20intermarried%20with%20the%20heathen%20(Nehemiah%2013%3A9-25).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EBecause%20Satan%20always%20returns%20to%20a%20house%20that%20is%20unoccupied%20even%20though%20cleansed%20(Matthew%2012%3A44)%2C%20we%20must%20guard%20our%20souls%20against%20his%20counterattacks.%20He%20is%20like%20a%20crocodile%20stalking%20its%20prey%2C%20probing%20for%20an%20opportunity%20to%20attack%20and%20waiting%20for%20the%20relaxation%20of%20vigilance.%20Let's%20stand%20our%20ground%20and%20watch%20carefully%2C%20throwing%20him%20out%20at%20the%20slightest%20sign%20of%20reentry!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Nehemiah.12:27-13:31",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3ENehemiah%2012%3A27-13%3A31%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_27%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDedication%20of%20Jerusalem%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Wall%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3EFor%20the%20dedication%20of%20the%20new%20wall%20of%20Jerusalem%2C%20the%20Levites%20throughout%20the%20land%20were%20asked%20to%20come%20to%20Jerusalem%20to%20assist%20in%20the%20ceremonies.%20They%20were%20to%20take%20part%20in%20the%20joyous%20occasion%20with%20their%20songs%20of%20thanksgiving%20and%20with%20the%20music%20of%20cymbals%2C%20harps%2C%20and%20lyres.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_28%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E28%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20singers%20were%20brought%20together%20from%20the%20region%20around%20Jerusalem%20and%20from%20the%20villages%20of%20the%20Netophathites.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_29%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E29%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20also%20came%20from%20Beth-gilgal%20and%20the%20rural%20areas%20near%20Geba%20and%20Azmaveth%2C%20for%20the%20singers%20had%20built%20their%20own%20settlements%20around%20Jerusalem.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_30%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2230%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E30%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20priests%20and%20Levites%20first%20purified%20themselves%3B%20then%20they%20purified%20the%20people%2C%20the%20gates%2C%20and%20the%20wall.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_31%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2231%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E31%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20led%20the%20leaders%20of%20Judah%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20wall%20and%20organized%20two%20large%20choirs%20to%20give%20thanks.%20One%20of%20the%20choirs%20proceeded%20southward%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E12%3A31%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eto%20the%20right.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20along%20the%20top%20of%20the%20wall%20to%20the%20Dung%20Gate.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_32%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2232%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E32%3C%2Fspan%3EHoshaiah%20and%20half%20the%20leaders%20of%20Judah%20followed%20them%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_33%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2233%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E33%3C%2Fspan%3Ealong%20with%20Azariah%2C%20Ezra%2C%20Meshullam%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_34%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2234%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E34%3C%2Fspan%3EJudah%2C%20Benjamin%2C%20Shemaiah%2C%20and%20Jeremiah.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_35%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2235%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E35%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20came%20some%20priests%20who%20played%20trumpets%2C%20including%20Zechariah%20son%20of%20Jonathan%2C%20son%20of%20Shemaiah%2C%20son%20of%20Mattaniah%2C%20son%20of%20Micaiah%2C%20son%20of%20Zaccur%2C%20a%20descendant%20of%20Asaph.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_36%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2236%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E36%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20Zechariah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20colleagues%20were%20Shemaiah%2C%20Azarel%2C%20Milalai%2C%20Gilalai%2C%20Maai%2C%20Nethanel%2C%20Judah%2C%20and%20Hanani.%20They%20used%20the%20musical%20instruments%20prescribed%20by%20David%2C%20the%20man%20of%20God.%20Ezra%20the%20scribe%20led%20this%20procession.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_37%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2237%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E37%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20the%20Fountain%20Gate%20they%20went%20straight%20up%20the%20steps%20on%20the%20ascent%20of%20the%20city%20wall%20toward%20the%20City%20of%20David.%20They%20passed%20the%20house%20of%20David%20and%20then%20proceeded%20to%20the%20Water%20Gate%20on%20the%20east.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_38%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2238%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E38%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20second%20choir%20giving%20thanks%20went%20northward%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E12%3A38%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eto%20the%20left.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20around%20the%20other%20way%20to%20meet%20them.%20I%20followed%20them%2C%20together%20with%20the%20other%20half%20of%20the%20people%2C%20along%20the%20top%20of%20the%20wall%20past%20the%20Tower%20of%20the%20Ovens%20to%20the%20Broad%20Wall%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_39%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2239%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E39%3C%2Fspan%3Ethen%20past%20the%20Ephraim%20Gate%20to%20the%20Old%20City%20Gate%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E12%3A39%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20Mishneh%20Gate%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20Jeshanah%20Gate.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20past%20the%20Fish%20Gate%20and%20the%20Tower%20of%20Hananel%2C%20and%20on%20to%20the%20Tower%20of%20the%20Hundred.%20Then%20we%20continued%20on%20to%20the%20Sheep%20Gate%20and%20stopped%20at%20the%20Guard%20Gate.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_40%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2240%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E40%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20two%20choirs%20that%20were%20giving%20thanks%20then%20proceeded%20to%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%2C%20where%20they%20took%20their%20places.%20So%20did%20I%2C%20together%20with%20the%20group%20of%20leaders%20who%20were%20with%20me.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_41%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2241%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E41%3C%2Fspan%3EWe%20went%20together%20with%20the%20trumpet-playing%20priests%26%23x2014%3BEliakim%2C%20Maaseiah%2C%20Miniamin%2C%20Micaiah%2C%20Elioenai%2C%20Zechariah%2C%20and%20Hananiah%26%23x2014%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_42%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2242%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E42%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20the%20singers%26%23x2014%3BMaaseiah%2C%20Shemaiah%2C%20Eleazar%2C%20Uzzi%2C%20Jehohanan%2C%20Malkijah%2C%20Elam%2C%20and%20Ezer.%20They%20played%20and%20sang%20loudly%20under%20the%20direction%20of%20Jezrahiah%20the%20choir%20director.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_43%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2243%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E43%3C%2Fspan%3EMany%20sacrifices%20were%20offered%20on%20that%20joyous%20day%2C%20for%20God%20had%20given%20the%20people%20cause%20for%20great%20joy.%20The%20women%20and%20children%20also%20participated%20in%20the%20celebration%2C%20and%20the%20joy%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Jerusalem%20could%20be%20heard%20far%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_44%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2244%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EProvisions%20for%20Temple%20Worship%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E44%3C%2Fspan%3EOn%20that%20day%20men%20were%20appointed%20to%20be%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20storerooms%20for%20the%20offerings%2C%20the%20first%20part%20of%20the%20harvest%2C%20and%20the%20tithes.%20They%20were%20responsible%20to%20collect%20from%20the%20fields%20outside%20the%20towns%20the%20portions%20required%20by%20the%20Law%20for%20the%20priests%20and%20Levites.%20For%20all%20the%20people%20of%20Judah%20took%20joy%20in%20the%20priests%20and%20Levites%20and%20their%20work.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_45%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2245%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E45%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20performed%20the%20service%20of%20their%20God%20and%20the%20service%20of%20purification%2C%20as%20commanded%20by%20David%20and%20his%20son%20Solomon%2C%20and%20so%20did%20the%20singers%20and%20the%20gatekeepers.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_46%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2246%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E46%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20custom%20of%20having%20choir%20directors%20to%20lead%20the%20choirs%20in%20hymns%20of%20praise%20and%20thanksgiving%20to%20God%20began%20long%20ago%20in%20the%20days%20of%20David%20and%20Asaph.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_12_47%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2247%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E47%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20now%2C%20in%20the%20days%20of%20Zerubbabel%20and%20of%20Nehemiah%2C%20all%20Israel%20brought%20a%20daily%20supply%20of%20food%20for%20the%20singers%2C%20the%20gatekeepers%2C%20and%20the%20Levites.%20The%20Levites%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20gave%20a%20portion%20of%20what%20they%20received%20to%20the%20priests%2C%20the%20descendants%20of%20Aaron.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_1%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3ENehemiah%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ENehemiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Various%20Reforms%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EOn%20that%20same%20day%2C%20as%20the%20Book%20of%20Moses%20was%20being%20read%20to%20the%20people%2C%20the%20passage%20was%20found%20that%20said%20no%20Ammonite%20or%20Moabite%20should%20ever%20be%20permitted%20to%20enter%20the%20assembly%20of%20God.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E13%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20See%20Deut%2023%3A3-6.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_2%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EFor%20they%20had%20not%20provided%20the%20Israelites%20with%20food%20and%20water%20in%20the%20wilderness.%20Instead%2C%20they%20hired%20Balaam%20to%20curse%20them%2C%20though%20our%20God%20turned%20the%20curse%20into%20a%20blessing.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_3%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20this%20passage%20of%20the%20Law%20was%20read%2C%20all%20those%20of%20foreign%20descent%20were%20immediately%20excluded%20from%20the%20assembly.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_4%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EBefore%20this%20had%20happened%2C%20Eliashib%20the%20priest%2C%20who%20had%20been%20appointed%20as%20supervisor%20of%20the%20storerooms%20of%20the%20Temple%20of%20our%20God%20and%20who%20was%20also%20a%20relative%20of%20Tobiah%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_5%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3Ehad%20converted%20a%20large%20storage%20room%20and%20placed%20it%20at%20Tobiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20disposal.%20The%20room%20had%20previously%20been%20used%20for%20storing%20the%20grain%20offerings%2C%20the%20frankincense%2C%20various%20articles%20for%20the%20Temple%2C%20and%20the%20tithes%20of%20grain%2C%20new%20wine%2C%20and%20olive%20oil%20(which%20were%20prescribed%20for%20the%20Levites%2C%20the%20singers%2C%20and%20the%20gatekeepers)%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20offerings%20for%20the%20priests.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_6%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20was%20not%20in%20Jerusalem%20at%20that%20time%2C%20for%20I%20had%20returned%20to%20King%20Artaxerxes%20of%20Babylon%20in%20the%20thirty-second%20year%20of%20his%20reign%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E13%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20King%20Artaxerxes%20of%20Persia%20is%20here%20identified%20as%20the%20king%20of%20Babylon%20because%20Persia%20had%20conquered%20the%20Babylonian%20Empire.%20The%20thirty-second%20year%20of%20Artaxerxes%20was%20433%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20though%20I%20later%20asked%20his%20permission%20to%20return.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_7%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20I%20arrived%20back%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20I%20learned%20about%20Eliashib%26%23x2019%3Bs%20evil%20deed%20in%20providing%20Tobiah%20with%20a%20room%20in%20the%20courtyards%20of%20the%20Temple%20of%20God.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_8%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20became%20very%20upset%20and%20threw%20all%20of%20Tobiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20belongings%20out%20of%20the%20room.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_9%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20I%20demanded%20that%20the%20rooms%20be%20purified%2C%20and%20I%20brought%20back%20the%20articles%20for%20God%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%2C%20the%20grain%20offerings%2C%20and%20the%20frankincense.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_10%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20also%20discovered%20that%20the%20Levites%20had%20not%20been%20given%20their%20prescribed%20portions%20of%20food%2C%20so%20they%20and%20the%20singers%20who%20were%20to%20conduct%20the%20worship%20services%20had%20all%20returned%20to%20work%20their%20fields.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_11%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20immediately%20confronted%20the%20leaders%20and%20demanded%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhy%20has%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%20been%20neglected%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20Then%20I%20called%20all%20the%20Levites%20back%20again%20and%20restored%20them%20to%20their%20proper%20duties.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_12%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20once%20more%20all%20the%20people%20of%20Judah%20began%20bringing%20their%20tithes%20of%20grain%2C%20new%20wine%2C%20and%20olive%20oil%20to%20the%20Temple%20storerooms.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_13%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20assigned%20supervisors%20for%20the%20storerooms%3A%20Shelemiah%20the%20priest%2C%20Zadok%20the%20scribe%2C%20and%20Pedaiah%2C%20one%20of%20the%20Levites.%20And%20I%20appointed%20Hanan%20son%20of%20Zaccur%20and%20grandson%20of%20Mattaniah%20as%20their%20assistant.%20These%20men%20had%20an%20excellent%20reputation%2C%20and%20it%20was%20their%20job%20to%20make%20honest%20distributions%20to%20their%20fellow%20Levites.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_14%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3ERemember%20this%20good%20deed%2C%20O%26%23xA0%3Bmy%20God%2C%20and%20do%20not%20forget%20all%20that%20I%20have%20faithfully%20done%20for%20the%20Temple%20of%20my%20God%20and%20its%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_15%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20those%20days%20I%20saw%20men%20of%20Judah%20treading%20out%20their%20winepresses%20on%20the%20Sabbath.%20They%20were%20also%20bringing%20in%20grain%2C%20loading%20it%20on%20donkeys%2C%20and%20bringing%20their%20wine%2C%20grapes%2C%20figs%2C%20and%20all%20sorts%20of%20produce%20to%20Jerusalem%20to%20sell%20on%20the%20Sabbath.%20So%20I%20rebuked%20them%20for%20selling%20their%20produce%20on%20that%20day.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_16%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3ESome%20men%20from%20Tyre%2C%20who%20lived%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20were%20bringing%20in%20fish%20and%20all%20kinds%20of%20merchandise.%20They%20were%20selling%20it%20on%20the%20Sabbath%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Judah%26%23x2014%3Band%20in%20Jerusalem%20at%20that!%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_17%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20I%20confronted%20the%20nobles%20of%20Judah.%20%26%23x201C%3BWhy%20are%20you%20profaning%20the%20Sabbath%20in%20this%20evil%20way%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20I%20asked.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_18%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWasn%26%23x2019%3Bt%20it%20just%20this%20sort%20of%20thing%20that%20your%20ancestors%20did%20that%20caused%20our%20God%20to%20bring%20all%20this%20trouble%20upon%20us%20and%20our%20city%3F%20Now%20you%20are%20bringing%20even%20more%20wrath%20upon%20Israel%20by%20permitting%20the%20Sabbath%20to%20be%20desecrated%20in%20this%20way!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_19%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20I%20commanded%20that%20the%20gates%20of%20Jerusalem%20should%20be%20shut%20as%20darkness%20fell%20every%20Friday%20evening%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E13%3A19%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eon%20the%20day%20before%20the%20Sabbath.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20not%20to%20be%20opened%20until%20the%20Sabbath%20ended.%20I%20sent%20some%20of%20my%20own%20servants%20to%20guard%20the%20gates%20so%20that%20no%20merchandise%20could%20be%20brought%20in%20on%20the%20Sabbath%20day.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_20%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20merchants%20and%20tradesmen%20with%20a%20variety%20of%20wares%20camped%20outside%20Jerusalem%20once%20or%20twice.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_21%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20I%20spoke%20sharply%20to%20them%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20are%20you%20doing%20out%20here%2C%20camping%20around%20the%20wall%3F%20If%20you%20do%20this%20again%2C%20I%20will%20arrest%20you!%26%23x201D%3B%20And%20that%20was%20the%20last%20time%20they%20came%20on%20the%20Sabbath.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22nehe_13_22%22%20bk%3D%22nehe%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20I%20commanded%20the%20Levites%20to%20purify%20themselves%20and%20to%20guard%20the%20gates%20in%